<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1346&amp;p=7001#p7001"><![CDATA[
But why should &quot;See more results&quot; be hidden if the Windows Search service is stopped? Only indexing gets disabled in Explorer. Real-time search continues to work. Although I understand Kilmatead's point about having &quot;See more results...&quot; optional, maybe it should have a checkbox that doesn't depend on the service. Something like &quot;Categorize search results and show link to see more results&quot; so users can get 3.6.x behavior and won't feel categories forced. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Sun Oct 06, 2013 8:33 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
