<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1346&amp;p=6996#p6996"><![CDATA[
Btw Kilmatead, how are you disabling Windows Search? By disabling the Search service or by uninstalling Windows Search from &quot;Turn Windows features on or off&quot; ? On Windows 8.1, I don't see the ability to remove Windows Search at all using &quot;Turn Windows features on or off&quot; so the only way to disable it on that OS might be to stop the service.<br /><br />When the service is stopped and disabled on either Windows 7 or Windows 8, &quot;See more results&quot; opens Explorer and continues to perform a real-time search. Only the indexing part is switched off. So in that case, &quot;See more results&quot; is not superfluous.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Sun Oct 06, 2013 6:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
